-- Koza Altin Buys Newmont's Turkey Gold Unit, Licenses for $8.5 Million
-- Seda Sezer
-- 2010-06-28T12:08:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/koza-altin-buys-newmont-s-turkey-gold-unit-licenses-for-8-5-million.html

          
          
             Koza Altin Isletmeleri AS, a Turkish
miner, bought the Turkish gold mining unit of Newmont Mining
Corp. for $8.5 million.  
 Newmont Altin Madencilik Limited Sirketi has 63 licenses
for gold mining in Turkey, Koza said in a filing with the
Istanbul Stock Exchange today.  
